Parsons Boulevard, west side, at 17th Avenue, showing greenhouses and a tree nursery, one of a number in this part of Whitestone. It was owned by Louis Dupay in 1909. The view is north from 19th Avenue and shows also (left) the pumping station of New York City's Whitestone water
works.
P. L. Sperr  April 13, 1927
